page.title: 17CONINGTON - YOUTH
page.content: Children do not have a lot to do. In summertime there is plenty of space to play,making tree houses for instance,or having picnics amongst the oaks.In the winter it is often possible to skate on the pond. Cycling is popular as many friends live outside the village. In the main, entertainment is found in each others houses, much to the annoyance of parents who long for a park. Infant and junior children go to Elsworth Primary school. Older children generally go to Swavesey Village College.
